  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting inclusion for visually impaired women</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fucho para Ciegos Puebla plans to develop 20 activities based on games and sports with at least 30 women with and without visual disability in Puebla, Mexico, promoting adapted sports with a gender perspective.  We plan the consolidation of the first soccer team for blind and visually impaired women &quot;Topas FC&quot;, made up of at least 12 women with and without visual disability that will strengthen their interpersonal relationships and improve their social skills such as self-esteem and autonomy.</narrative>
  </description>
